               <summary>The manuscript consists of two texts. First is Adhyātmarāmāyaṇa 
and the second is Hālāsyamāhātmya of Skandapurāṇa. Both are complete and according to the information both are written by diffrent scribes.  Folio are numbered independently. Adhyātmarāmāyaṇa has 124 folio and Hālāsyamāhātmya has 123 folio. 
Adhyātmarāmāyaṇa is written by śivaśaṃkaran and the Hālāsyamāhātmya is written by Govinda Vaiṣṇava.

